1
00:00:01,106 --> 00:00:02,649
[♪ upbeat music plays]

2
00:00:30,427 --> 00:00:34,056
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

3
00:00:44,149 --> 00:00:46,860
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION - SOME
SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

4
00:00:46,943 --> 00:00:49,071
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:49,154 --> 00:00:51,156
[♪ gentle music plays]

6
00:00:53,116 --> 00:00:54,117
Hwayeong.

7
00:01:22,688 --> 00:01:26,733
[♪ tense music plays]

8
00:01:34,741 --> 00:01:37,369
[♪ melancholy ballad plays]

9
00:01:52,592 --> 00:01:54,719
[song continues]

10
00:02:15,532 --> 00:02:17,826
[music distorts, stutters]

11
00:02:19,786 --> 00:02:21,538
-[device beeps]
-[automated voice, in English] Power off.

12
00:02:21,621 --> 00:02:23,165
[in Korean] Just listen to it.

13
00:02:25,876 --> 00:02:28,295
Come on, just try listening to it for now.

14
00:02:28,378 --> 00:02:30,464
Music is good for treating anxiety.

15
00:02:31,423 --> 00:02:32,758
It's out of battery.

16
00:02:32,841 --> 00:02:34,384
Huh?

17
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:38,221
I charged it yesterday, though.
Give me a second.

18
00:02:38,305 --> 00:02:40,766
-I should have a power bank.
-[announcer] …is now departing.

19
00:02:41,349 --> 00:02:42,768
Do you want to chew on this?

20
00:02:44,269 --> 00:02:47,355
Chewing on something can help you relax.

21
00:02:50,859 --> 00:02:52,611
I told you I'm okay.

22
00:02:53,695 --> 00:02:55,655
You're not okay, though.

23
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:58,742
You were crying yesterday.

24
00:02:58,825 --> 00:03:01,870
Excuse me, please wake up.

25
00:03:01,953 --> 00:03:03,330
Seonu…

26
00:03:03,413 --> 00:03:04,414
Sorry?

27
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,001
Seonu…

28
00:03:09,377 --> 00:03:10,629
You were saying "Seonu."

29
00:03:11,379 --> 00:03:13,673
[♪ somber music plays]

30
00:03:19,721 --> 00:03:20,931
Do you know me?

31
00:03:21,723 --> 00:03:22,933
Sorry?

32
00:03:23,016 --> 00:03:24,684
Did I ever ask for your help?

33
00:03:26,436 --> 00:03:27,437
Ah…

34
00:03:28,021 --> 00:03:30,106
Well, no, but I--

35
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:33,109
I'm sorry you had to help me
like that yesterday, but…

36
00:03:34,528 --> 00:03:35,946
I never asked for your help.

37
00:03:37,405 --> 00:03:40,200
So just be on your way
and stop crossing the line.

38
00:03:41,076 --> 00:03:42,452
[stammers] What?
STYLE
::cue()

39
00:03:46,706 --> 00:03:49,709
Wait, when did I ever cross the…

40
00:03:49,793 --> 00:03:51,002
[ship horn blowing]

41
00:03:51,086 --> 00:03:52,671
Excuse me!

42
00:03:58,385 --> 00:03:59,594
[sighs]

43
00:04:01,346 --> 00:04:02,472
What the hell? Sheesh.

44
00:04:03,848 --> 00:04:08,228
Hey, I need to get on a ferry right away,
so I'm going to need a prescription.

45
00:04:08,311 --> 00:04:10,021
-[horn honks]
-I'll head to your hospital.

46
00:04:10,105 --> 00:04:11,773
I'm heading over right now.

47
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,484
[ship horn blowing]

48
00:04:14,568 --> 00:04:15,986
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

49
00:04:16,069 --> 00:04:18,113
[Ms. Hwang] The last ferry came
and went ages ago.

50
00:04:18,196 --> 00:04:20,365
How come Dr. Do Jiui still isn't here?

51
00:04:20,448 --> 00:04:24,411
I know. He couldn't have deserted his post
on his first day, right?

52
00:04:24,494 --> 00:04:26,621
-Sheesh.
-By the way, Ms. Hwang,

53
00:04:26,705 --> 00:04:28,707
a newbie is joining us next week, right?

54
00:04:28,790 --> 00:04:32,085
I'm going to be really nice to her.

55
00:04:32,168 --> 00:04:33,378
Newbie?

56
00:04:34,254 --> 00:04:38,216
You said the new nurse
is in her third year. I'm in my fourth.

57
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,302
Doesn't that make her the newbie?

58
00:04:40,385 --> 00:04:42,762
[chuckles] I guess you're right,

59
00:04:42,846 --> 00:04:45,473
but she won't be your typical newbie,
just so you know.

60
00:04:45,557 --> 00:04:47,642
She hasn't even been a nurse
for that long,

61
00:04:47,726 --> 00:04:49,519
so imagine how awkward she'll feel.

62
00:04:49,603 --> 00:04:51,396
I should help her out.

63
00:04:51,479 --> 00:04:54,608
I've even organized
all the handover notes.

64
00:04:54,691 --> 00:04:58,028
-Oh, okay. Well done.
-[chuckles]

65
00:04:58,862 --> 00:05:02,073
As to who will end up helping whom,
we won't know until she gets here,

66
00:05:02,157 --> 00:05:03,742
but well done.

67
00:05:03,825 --> 00:05:05,619
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

68
00:05:05,702 --> 00:05:07,078
[grunts] Dr. Do.

69
00:05:07,162 --> 00:05:08,830
Hmm, what?

70
00:05:08,914 --> 00:05:12,918
Goodness, Dr. Do!
Do you have any idea what time…

71
00:05:13,001 --> 00:05:17,464
My gosh. You look like death.
What happened to you?

72
00:05:17,547 --> 00:05:20,550
I'm sorry. I fell asleep on the ferry.

73
00:05:21,468 --> 00:05:24,137
So you were sleeping on the ferry
all this time?

74
00:05:25,472 --> 00:05:26,473
Yes.

75
00:05:26,556 --> 00:05:29,684
[scoffs] Must be nice being
that unbothered.

76
00:05:29,768 --> 00:05:32,187
Sleeping fine while ditching work.

77
00:05:42,781 --> 00:05:45,116
-[♪ gentle music plays]
-[Hari] Do you want to chew on this?

78
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,578
Chewing on something can help you relax.

79
00:05:49,079 --> 00:05:51,122
FEELING DOWN?
HERE'S A PICK-ME-UP!

80
00:05:55,335 --> 00:05:56,544
[sighs]

81
00:06:07,806 --> 00:06:13,603
EPISODE 2
THE WOMAN WHO CROSSES THE LINE

82
00:06:13,687 --> 00:06:14,896
[music ends]

83
00:06:16,648 --> 00:06:18,817
-[Jiui] Bellflower roots?
-That's right.

84
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:22,112
-They're precious wild bellflower roots.
-Mmm.

85
00:06:22,195 --> 00:06:25,115
So, about that…
You saved the chief's life last week,

86
00:06:25,198 --> 00:06:28,368
so the youth association
told me to give it to you.

87
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,454
It's from the youth association?
Thank you.

88
00:06:31,538 --> 00:06:32,914
[coughing]

89
00:06:35,709 --> 00:06:38,712
By the way, Mr. Lee Jangsu,
what brings you in today?

90
00:06:38,795 --> 00:06:42,632
I'm just here
to get those meds I always take.

91
00:06:42,716 --> 00:06:44,926
Those meds you always take? [sighs]

92
00:06:45,010 --> 00:06:47,762
[coughing]

93
00:06:47,846 --> 00:06:50,348
You already took
two weeks' worth a week ago.

94
00:06:50,432 --> 00:06:53,685
Two weeks' worth
will barely cut it anymore.

95
00:06:53,768 --> 00:06:56,771
My wife also takes it and all,

96
00:06:56,855 --> 00:07:00,650
so give us about
a month's worth this time.

97
00:07:01,234 --> 00:07:04,070
Did you just say you share your meds
with your wife?

98
00:07:04,154 --> 00:07:05,780
Yes.

99
00:07:05,864 --> 00:07:07,782
No. Proxy prescriptions are illegal.

100
00:07:07,866 --> 00:07:10,243
Strictly speaking,
it's not a proxy prescription,

101
00:07:10,326 --> 00:07:12,787
since I'm also taking those meds.

102
00:07:12,871 --> 00:07:13,872
I still can't do it.

103
00:07:13,955 --> 00:07:17,542
And the coughing might turn into pneumonia
if it continues for two weeks or more,

104
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:19,169
so I'll give you three days' worth.

105
00:07:19,252 --> 00:07:20,962
Come back after finishing it.

106
00:07:21,045 --> 00:07:23,047
I'm busy as hell because of the anchovies!

107
00:07:23,131 --> 00:07:25,383
And you expect me to visit regularly?

108
00:07:26,009 --> 00:07:28,678
That's the only way I can properly
assess your condition, sir.

109
00:07:28,762 --> 00:07:31,931
I know my condition best.
STYLE
::cue()

110
00:07:32,015 --> 00:07:33,641
I'll take care of myself,

111
00:07:33,725 --> 00:07:35,310
so just give me 30 days' worth.

112
00:07:36,603 --> 00:07:38,605
-I can't do that.
-That's how it's always been!

113
00:07:38,688 --> 00:07:40,523
You're just going to cut me off like this?

114
00:07:40,607 --> 00:07:42,984
[Ms. Hwang] Cough medicine,
something for your phlegm,

115
00:07:43,067 --> 00:07:46,070
antibiotics, and this long one is
the stomach coating agent.

116
00:07:46,154 --> 00:07:49,657
Take one packet in the morning
and in the evening after a meal.

117
00:07:49,741 --> 00:07:53,203
[grunts] Did you really
only put three days' worth in there?

118
00:07:54,037 --> 00:07:55,038
[chuckles]

119
00:07:55,121 --> 00:07:58,625
We only put in
as much as the doctor prescribed.

120
00:07:58,708 --> 00:08:01,044
That's the law.

121
00:08:01,127 --> 00:08:04,964
Is there a law saying
civil servants can ignore residents?

122
00:08:05,048 --> 00:08:07,383
Who said anything about ignoring anyone?

123
00:08:07,467 --> 00:08:10,720
That's not it. It's just how the law is.

124
00:08:10,804 --> 00:08:12,430
Hey, you think I don't know the law?

125
00:08:12,514 --> 00:08:14,140
Law this, law that!

126
00:08:14,724 --> 00:08:18,394
Looks like I'll have to take legal action
against you civil servants

127
00:08:18,478 --> 00:08:20,480
who love the law so much
as a wake-up call!

128
00:08:20,563 --> 00:08:21,648
Wait!

129
00:08:21,731 --> 00:08:24,984
Have you been drinking?
Calm down a little, so I can explain…

130
00:08:32,617 --> 00:08:34,327
-What should we do?
-Sorry?

131
00:08:34,911 --> 00:08:38,581
Word is Mr. Lee actually went to
the county office to file a complaint.

132
00:08:38,665 --> 00:08:39,791
Ah.

133
00:08:39,874 --> 00:08:42,502
[nurse] Looks like things will get
quite troublesome for a while.

134
00:08:46,297 --> 00:08:49,300
Doc, loosen up a little, will you?

135
00:08:49,968 --> 00:08:53,930
Duking it out with the residents
is never easy.

136
00:08:54,514 --> 00:08:56,141
It can't be helped.

137
00:08:56,224 --> 00:08:58,560
-Thank you for the meal.
-Thank you.

138
00:08:59,435 --> 00:09:01,187
Which brings us to my point.

139
00:09:01,771 --> 00:09:05,275
If it won't be a big issue,
how about we just do as they ask?

140
00:09:05,358 --> 00:09:07,026
That's better for everyone, no?

141
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:10,572
Giving patients
whatever prescriptions they ask for

142
00:09:10,655 --> 00:09:12,532
isn't necessarily "better for everyone."

143
00:09:12,615 --> 00:09:14,617
Nothing good comes
from giving in to patients.

144
00:09:17,829 --> 00:09:19,789
I'm not saying this for my own good, okay?

145
00:09:19,873 --> 00:09:21,624
It's because I'm worried about you guys.

146
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:23,376
If you keep doing as you please,

147
00:09:23,459 --> 00:09:25,670
something terrible is
going to happen to you!

148
00:09:26,212 --> 00:09:27,797
You'll see once it happens to you.

149
00:09:27,881 --> 00:09:29,507
-Gosh, so frustrating.
-What do you…

150
00:09:29,591 --> 00:09:30,592
[Mr. Park] Is anyone in?

151
00:09:30,675 --> 00:09:32,343
-[Ms. Hwang] Oh, my!
-[Jucheon] Huh?

152
00:09:33,094 --> 00:09:34,345
[Ms. Hwang] Oh, goodness!

153
00:09:35,513 --> 00:09:37,098
I see you were still eating.

154
00:09:37,182 --> 00:09:38,349
-Hello.
-[Ms. Hwang] Goodness.

155
00:09:38,433 --> 00:09:41,102
You were discharged
from the hospital already?

156
00:09:41,186 --> 00:09:42,270
[chuckling] Yes.

157
00:09:42,353 --> 00:09:45,148
I got treated right away, after all.

158
00:09:45,231 --> 00:09:48,651
-Dr. Do's stubbornness saved my life.
-[Ms. Hwang laughs]

159
00:09:48,735 --> 00:09:53,489
Had it not been for Dr. Do Jiui,
I'd be on my way to Heaven by now.

160
00:09:53,573 --> 00:09:55,283
[Ms. Hwang, Mr. Park chuckling]

161
00:09:55,366 --> 00:09:57,410
[Mr. Park sighs] My, my, my.

162
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:01,456
[Ms. Hwang exclaims]
Isn't this monkfish liver?

163
00:10:01,539 --> 00:10:02,999
What a precious treat!

164
00:10:03,082 --> 00:10:05,627
Not as precious as my own life.

165
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:07,545
[Ms. Hwang, Mr. Park chuckling]

166
00:10:08,796 --> 00:10:10,840
Goodness, Dr. Do.

167
00:10:11,549 --> 00:10:13,301
Thank you so much.

168
00:10:13,384 --> 00:10:16,930
Once I make a full recovery,
I'll pay you back for everything.

169
00:10:17,013 --> 00:10:18,473
You can count on it. [laughs]

170
00:10:18,556 --> 00:10:19,599
Okay.

171
00:10:20,183 --> 00:10:23,102
We took too much of your time
when you were eating.

172
00:10:23,186 --> 00:10:25,355
-Let's go now, Chunsik.
-That's right.

173
00:10:25,438 --> 00:10:27,690
You must be tired
since you just got discharged,

174
00:10:27,774 --> 00:10:30,318
-so go home to rest up.
-Okay.

175
00:10:30,401 --> 00:10:32,946
-Thank you, everyone. [chuckles]
-Goodbye.

176
00:10:33,029 --> 00:10:36,699
-Take care.
-[Ms. Hwang] Oh my, thank you.

177
00:10:36,783 --> 00:10:39,035
-Have a safe trip home.
-[Mr. Park] Sure.

178
00:10:39,118 --> 00:10:40,662
I love you, Dr. Do.

179
00:10:40,745 --> 00:10:41,746
What?

180
00:10:41,829 --> 00:10:44,707
You're totally
in the chief's good graces now.

181
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:48,044
On this island,
once you get on his good side,

182
00:10:48,127 --> 00:10:50,004
your quality of life skyrockets.

183
00:10:50,088 --> 00:10:52,465
Last time, he brought me pizza
from the mainland

184
00:10:52,548 --> 00:10:54,425
because he liked my acupuncture treatment.

185
00:10:55,134 --> 00:10:57,136
[chuckles] I got pizza for acupuncture,

186
00:10:57,220 --> 00:11:00,348
so can you imagine how well
he'd treat you for saving his life?

187
00:11:00,431 --> 00:11:01,516
Pizza?

188
00:11:01,599 --> 00:11:03,893
Just because
he liked your acupuncture treatment?

189
00:11:03,977 --> 00:11:05,520
Yes! Pizza!

190
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:07,188
[Jiui chuckles]

191
00:11:07,272 --> 00:11:10,233
[♪ playful music plays]

192
00:11:11,234 --> 00:11:12,819
-What the heck?
-[clears throat]
STYLE
::cue()

193
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:18,032
[sighs] Let's see…

194
00:11:24,789 --> 00:11:25,873
[exclaims]

195
00:11:30,753 --> 00:11:33,172
Ms. Eom. What's going on here?

196
00:11:33,256 --> 00:11:34,382
What now?

197
00:11:34,465 --> 00:11:37,343
I mean your slippers.
They're the same as mine.

198
00:11:38,636 --> 00:11:41,097
Did you pay a premium
for the overseas shipping too?

199
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:44,183
I heard these were really hard to get.

200
00:11:45,059 --> 00:11:46,853
A premium?

201
00:11:49,022 --> 00:11:50,023
Let me see now.

202
00:11:51,149 --> 00:11:52,150
[exclaims]

203
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:54,736
Did they always have this color?

204
00:11:54,819 --> 00:11:56,654
I've never seen it before.

205
00:11:56,738 --> 00:11:59,991
What are you, a detective?
What are you looking at my feet for?

206
00:12:00,575 --> 00:12:02,827
I'm just fascinated, that's all.

207
00:12:03,494 --> 00:12:06,122
I think we have pretty similar taste.

208
00:12:06,205 --> 00:12:07,749
Similar, my ass.

209
00:12:07,832 --> 00:12:11,294
How could I possibly have similar taste
to someone who owns a clinic in Seoul?

210
00:12:12,462 --> 00:12:13,755
Just get back to work!

211
00:12:15,048 --> 00:12:16,382
[Ms. Eom huffs]

212
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:20,887
He's such a weirdo! [sighs]

213
00:12:22,221 --> 00:12:23,514
Damn it!

214
00:12:25,058 --> 00:12:28,102
Who the hell pays a premium
for a flimsy pair of slippers?

215
00:12:28,186 --> 00:12:33,149
I do not like him one bit. [exclaims]

216
00:12:40,907 --> 00:12:42,241
[grunts]

217
00:12:43,117 --> 00:12:44,410
[stomach growling]

218
00:12:45,161 --> 00:12:46,496
[groans]

219
00:12:50,458 --> 00:12:51,751
[groans] I'm so hungry.

220
00:12:51,834 --> 00:12:53,795
[phone chiming]

221
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:02,929
[doctor 1] It's only 8:00 p.m.,
but none of the stores are open…

222
00:13:03,012 --> 00:13:04,722
[doctor 2] Our island only has
one supermarket.

223
00:13:04,806 --> 00:13:06,474
[doctor 3] Ours doesn't even open
at times.

224
00:13:06,557 --> 00:13:09,018
I realized the value
of convenience stores.

225
00:13:09,102 --> 00:13:11,562
[doctor 4] If you come across these
on your next trip to the market,

226
00:13:11,646 --> 00:13:13,022
you have to stockpile them.

227
00:13:13,106 --> 00:13:17,276
They rarely stock up on beer,
so finders keepers.

228
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,820
[doctor 1] I should rush over there now!

229
00:13:18,903 --> 00:13:21,072
Some beer to keep me company
on these long nights!

230
00:13:21,155 --> 00:13:23,491
Oh, beer…

231
00:13:25,034 --> 00:13:26,744
Beer.

232
00:13:28,246 --> 00:13:29,622
[sighs]

233
00:13:31,332 --> 00:13:34,502
[clicks tongue]
They don't have any ales or IPAs, though.

234
00:13:36,921 --> 00:13:39,382
I wonder if the chief
would get some for me.

235
00:13:39,465 --> 00:13:41,342
[chuckles]

236
00:13:41,425 --> 00:13:44,470
Hey, I got here first.
You can't just take them all like that.

237
00:13:44,554 --> 00:13:46,347
-Hey…
-Granny, put these on my tab!

238
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:47,473
Okay.

239
00:13:47,557 --> 00:13:48,850
Goodbye!

240
00:13:49,559 --> 00:13:52,311
Excuse me, do you have any more beer?

241
00:13:52,395 --> 00:13:53,563
No, that was it.

242
00:13:53,646 --> 00:13:55,231
Wow, I can't even.

243
00:13:56,190 --> 00:13:57,400
What the hell?

244
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:00,403
[♪ playful music plays]

245
00:14:00,486 --> 00:14:03,489
LUCKY SUPERMARKET

246
00:14:06,868 --> 00:14:08,035
[Hari] Mmm.

247
00:14:09,745 --> 00:14:11,122
You drink every day?

248
00:14:11,789 --> 00:14:15,126
Man, what's that voice I hear?
It seems to be crossing a line.

249
00:14:16,878 --> 00:14:20,381
You probably shouldn't be drinking.
If you drink like that every day…

250
00:14:23,926 --> 00:14:25,636
It's just bad for you.

251
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,764
I'm guessing that's a roundabout way
of telling me to hand some over.

252
00:14:28,848 --> 00:14:30,558
But stop crossing the line, okay?

253
00:14:30,641 --> 00:14:32,685
-That's not it. I just--
-Hey.

254
00:14:35,146 --> 00:14:37,064
Do you know how suspicious you are?

255
00:14:38,065 --> 00:14:39,066
What do you mean?

256
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:41,485
I mean, why do we keep
running into each other?

257
00:14:42,695 --> 00:14:44,030
Are you…

258
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:46,324
a stalker?

259
00:14:46,407 --> 00:14:48,159
[stammers] A stalker?

260
00:14:49,619 --> 00:14:52,079
Listen, you're the one
who's always butting in, okay?

261
00:14:52,163 --> 00:14:54,540
I boarded the ferry first,
and I also came here first.

262
00:14:54,624 --> 00:14:56,250
So if we're talking about stalking,

263
00:14:56,334 --> 00:14:58,085
I'd say you fit the profile more.

264
00:14:59,545 --> 00:15:00,546
If not, never mind.

265
00:15:02,006 --> 00:15:03,007
"If not, never"…

266
00:15:05,927 --> 00:15:07,094
[chuckles, scoffs]

267
00:15:10,223 --> 00:15:14,018
[exclaims, distorted]

268
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,314
[both grunting]

269
00:15:25,905 --> 00:15:27,990
Look at me. I almost crossed the line.

270
00:15:29,659 --> 00:15:30,660
[exclaims]

271
00:15:36,499 --> 00:15:38,876
[groaning]
STYLE
::cue()

272
00:15:47,134 --> 00:15:48,177
[gasps]

273
00:15:50,179 --> 00:15:51,639
What the hell?

274
00:15:53,891 --> 00:15:54,892
Hello.

275
00:15:55,476 --> 00:15:58,062
[Jiui sighs] So she's a nurse.

276
00:15:59,105 --> 00:16:00,898
-[sighs]
-Say hello, everyone.

277
00:16:00,982 --> 00:16:02,650
This is Ms. Yuk Hari.

278
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:06,654
I'm Eom Jeongseon, a fourth-year nurse.

279
00:16:06,737 --> 00:16:08,823
You're third-year… so, class of '19?

280
00:16:08,906 --> 00:16:10,366
I was in the class of '18.

281
00:16:10,449 --> 00:16:13,786
Yes, class of '19.
I'm sure I have a lot to learn from you.

282
00:16:13,869 --> 00:16:16,247
Right. I look forward to working with you.

283
00:16:16,330 --> 00:16:18,249
[Ms. Hwang]
A lot to learn from her? Please.

284
00:16:18,332 --> 00:16:23,004
Ms. Hari here is an intellectual who used
to work in a university hospital's ER.

285
00:16:23,087 --> 00:16:25,047
Not just any hospital, but Asong Hospital.

286
00:16:25,131 --> 00:16:28,509
I'm sure the operating room
was practically her living room.

287
00:16:28,592 --> 00:16:31,762
But still, isn't this her first time
at a public health center?

288
00:16:31,846 --> 00:16:34,390
Mmm. It may be her first time,

289
00:16:34,473 --> 00:16:37,143
but ever since she was a kid,
she visited the island every holiday,

290
00:16:37,226 --> 00:16:39,562
so she's well-acquainted with Pyeondongdo.

291
00:16:39,645 --> 00:16:43,357
Wow, then you must be
really close to the villagers here.

292
00:16:43,441 --> 00:16:44,775
That's great.

293
00:16:44,859 --> 00:16:47,903
I think it's way harder
to get close to the villagers here

294
00:16:47,987 --> 00:16:49,447
than it is to work here.

295
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:51,907
That's because you slack off all the time.

296
00:16:51,991 --> 00:16:54,118
I'm Yong Jucheon
of the Korean Medicine Ward.

297
00:16:54,201 --> 00:16:56,787
[Hari chuckles] I look forward
to working with you.

298
00:16:56,871 --> 00:17:00,791
And this here is Dr. Do Jiui, the surgeon.

299
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:05,463
He's the very man
you busted your ass carrying over here.

300
00:17:05,546 --> 00:17:06,839
[exclaims]

301
00:17:07,631 --> 00:17:09,258
So you're a doctor.

302
00:17:09,342 --> 00:17:10,426
Uh, yes.

303
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:12,595
[Ms. Hwang] Huh?

304
00:17:13,387 --> 00:17:15,431
Have you already greeted each other?

305
00:17:15,514 --> 00:17:16,807
[chuckles]

306
00:17:16,891 --> 00:17:21,062
Well, I don't know if I can say that.

307
00:17:21,145 --> 00:17:22,730
It might be crossing a line.

308
00:17:23,898 --> 00:17:25,608
[Ms. Hwang] What are you talking about?

309
00:17:29,236 --> 00:17:30,363
I'm Hyeon Chiyeon.

310
00:17:31,155 --> 00:17:32,948
I look forward to working with you.

311
00:17:33,616 --> 00:17:35,993
Now then, doctors,
please get ready to see patients.

312
00:17:36,077 --> 00:17:37,703
-Okay.
-As for us,

313
00:17:37,787 --> 00:17:40,456
let me just pull you aside
for a quick chat. This way.

314
00:17:41,248 --> 00:17:42,875
[Hyeon] Never expected to see her here.

315
00:17:43,376 --> 00:17:45,711
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

316
00:17:45,795 --> 00:17:47,880
[Ms. Hwang, Hari chuckling]

317
00:17:47,963 --> 00:17:53,260
My, you used to be so tiny,
but you've grown so much.

318
00:17:53,344 --> 00:17:56,681
But why did you come here
from such a good university hospital?

319
00:17:57,306 --> 00:17:58,307
Ah…

320
00:17:59,058 --> 00:18:00,559
Well…

321
00:18:00,643 --> 00:18:04,522
I was just wondering why you came
all the way to this island from the city.

322
00:18:04,605 --> 00:18:06,065
If there was a story behind it.

323
00:18:07,358 --> 00:18:10,236
-I just wanted to take a break.
-Mmm.

324
00:18:10,945 --> 00:18:12,321
Take a break?

325
00:18:12,405 --> 00:18:13,489
Right.

326
00:18:13,572 --> 00:18:15,032
Let's do that.

327
00:18:15,116 --> 00:18:17,702
-Take it slow and easy.
-[Hari] Mmm.

328
00:18:17,785 --> 00:18:19,203
-[chuckles]
-[phone ringing]

329
00:18:19,286 --> 00:18:22,623
-Let's catch up again later.
-Uh-huh.

330
00:18:22,707 --> 00:18:23,833
[ringing stops]

331
00:18:23,916 --> 00:18:27,253
This is Hwang Sinhye from
the Public Health Center speaking.

332
00:18:27,336 --> 00:18:33,384
Though working here may look peaceful,
it's actually a war zone,

333
00:18:33,467 --> 00:18:37,596
and the work we do is just as complicated
as working in an operating room.

334
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,266
It's not the kind of place
where you can just take a break,

335
00:18:40,349 --> 00:18:42,017
is all I'm saying.

336
00:18:42,101 --> 00:18:44,979
I see. [chuckles]
I look forward to your guidance.

337
00:18:45,062 --> 00:18:46,313
-Mm-hmm.
-Ah!

338
00:18:46,397 --> 00:18:47,773
What should I do first?

339
00:18:49,024 --> 00:18:50,025
Ooh…

340
00:18:51,318 --> 00:18:52,319
[stammers]

341
00:18:52,403 --> 00:18:55,656
Why don't you start by switching out
the toilet paper rolls in the bathroom?

342
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,241
Ah…

343
00:18:58,117 --> 00:18:59,118
Toilet paper?

344
00:19:01,537 --> 00:19:03,372
Okay. [chuckles]

345
00:19:04,331 --> 00:19:05,833
-This way?
-Mm-hmm.

346
00:19:05,916 --> 00:19:07,501
[Ms. Hwang chattering]

347
00:19:11,005 --> 00:19:14,508
Why on earth did I mention toilet paper,
after putting on such a front?

348
00:19:15,217 --> 00:19:16,218
[gasps]

349
00:19:20,890 --> 00:19:22,683
[sighs]

350
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:23,934
[mouse clicking]

351
00:19:25,019 --> 00:19:26,187
[no audible dialogue]

352
00:19:34,153 --> 00:19:35,404
[sighs]

353
00:19:35,488 --> 00:19:37,156
Of all people, why…

354
00:19:38,324 --> 00:19:41,076
Dr. Jiui, you're going to
have to go somewhere.

355
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,662
It's a patient who just had
a cancer operation,

356
00:19:43,746 --> 00:19:45,748
but his daughter's
having trouble reaching him.

357
00:19:45,831 --> 00:19:47,666
She's asking if we can check in on him.

358
00:19:48,834 --> 00:19:51,545
-Me?
-Who else? Should I go?

359
00:19:51,629 --> 00:19:53,297
I don't know my way around yet.

360
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:56,300
Don't worry about that.
We'll send another person with you.

361
00:19:56,884 --> 00:19:58,552
All settled, right? Mm-mmm.

362
00:19:58,636 --> 00:19:59,804
[♪ playful music plays]

363
00:20:01,055 --> 00:20:02,097
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

364
00:20:11,732 --> 00:20:13,692
[metal creaking]

365
00:20:15,528 --> 00:20:16,946
Oh, gosh.

366
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:22,701
[boat approaching]

367
00:20:34,255 --> 00:20:35,422
Easy, easy!

368
00:20:37,508 --> 00:20:38,551
Seriously…

369
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:40,261
Hello!

370
00:20:40,344 --> 00:20:42,555
[captain] Hey!
Looks like it's starting to drizzle.

371
00:20:42,638 --> 00:20:43,722
[Hari] I know, right?

372
00:20:43,806 --> 00:20:46,600
Sir, you said it was nearby.
Why do we need a boat?

373
00:20:46,684 --> 00:20:48,936
It's only five minutes away by boat.

374
00:20:49,603 --> 00:20:50,646
Oh, come on…

375
00:20:50,729 --> 00:20:52,273
[captain] What business do you have there?

376
00:20:52,356 --> 00:20:54,859
A patient's guardian
requested a home visit.

377
00:20:54,942 --> 00:20:56,944
A patient on that side? Who's sick?

378
00:20:57,027 --> 00:20:58,529
Do you know Mr. Kim Jeongbae?

379
00:20:58,612 --> 00:21:00,322
Kim Jeongbae? Who could that be?

380
00:21:01,156 --> 00:21:03,158
Oh, that guy?

381
00:21:03,242 --> 00:21:05,786
I guess it's the guy who keeps to himself.

382
00:21:05,870 --> 00:21:08,747
But I don't think it'll be easy
getting in that house.

383
00:21:09,331 --> 00:21:12,793
The guy seemed to really hate
people entering his house.

384
00:21:13,377 --> 00:21:14,461
Oh…

385
00:21:14,545 --> 00:21:16,672
So he hates it when people cross the line,

386
00:21:17,506 --> 00:21:18,757
like someone I know.

387
00:21:19,258 --> 00:21:20,259
[captain] What?

388
00:21:20,342 --> 00:21:22,970
Ah, it's nothing.
We can go there now, right?

389
00:21:23,053 --> 00:21:25,097
-Of course. Get in.
-[stammers] Wait.

390
00:21:26,307 --> 00:21:29,101
[stammers] Isn't there
some other way there?

391
00:21:29,184 --> 00:21:30,644
Some other way?

392
00:21:31,979 --> 00:21:34,231
Well, they are connected.

393
00:21:34,315 --> 00:21:37,610
But if you were to walk,
it would take at least 40 minutes.

394
00:21:37,693 --> 00:21:40,029
With the mountain path
being really hilly and all. [laughs]

395
00:21:40,112 --> 00:21:42,907
Who would be dumb enough to do that?

396
00:21:42,990 --> 00:21:44,575
[captain, Hari laugh]

397
00:21:44,658 --> 00:21:47,202
Forty minutes? Okay.

398
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:50,664
Wait, Dr. Do. You're going to walk there?

399
00:21:50,748 --> 00:21:53,667
You take the boat.
I'll walk. See you there.

400
00:21:53,751 --> 00:21:55,753
Wait… [stammering]

401
00:21:55,836 --> 00:21:57,379
Doctor!

402
00:21:57,963 --> 00:22:00,341
[♪ playful music plays]

403
00:22:00,424 --> 00:22:02,843
Where the heck am I? Damn it.

404
00:22:05,095 --> 00:22:06,805
[panting]

405
00:22:08,432 --> 00:22:09,892
[Hari] Hey, wait up.

406
00:22:14,939 --> 00:22:17,149
[panting] We could have been there
in five minutes.

407
00:22:17,232 --> 00:22:19,068
Why punish ourselves by walking there?

408
00:22:19,151 --> 00:22:21,779
I never asked you to come with me, okay?

409
00:22:21,862 --> 00:22:23,989
You could have just taken the boat.

410
00:22:24,073 --> 00:22:26,742
It's not like there's anything I can do
without a doctor.

411
00:22:26,825 --> 00:22:28,786
Why should I go there by myself?

412
00:22:31,413 --> 00:22:32,414
I was talking to myself.

413
00:22:35,209 --> 00:22:38,128
Tells me not to cross the line
but gives me so many causes for concern.

414
00:22:38,212 --> 00:22:39,838
-Ms. Yuk.
-Okay, okay.

415
00:22:39,922 --> 00:22:41,590
I'll stop talking to myself.

416
00:22:41,674 --> 00:22:44,259
Hurry up. [groans]

417
00:22:54,061 --> 00:22:57,064
Haven't you been here before, Ms. Hari?

418
00:22:57,147 --> 00:22:59,400
Who would walk here?
Everyone takes a boat.

419
00:23:00,859 --> 00:23:01,860
Let me see.

420
00:23:05,739 --> 00:23:07,366
[insect chittering]

421
00:23:07,449 --> 00:23:08,701
[screams]

422
00:23:09,952 --> 00:23:11,245
Hey, will you please…

423
00:23:11,829 --> 00:23:14,289
That's not it. Your shoulder, Dr. Do…

424
00:23:15,249 --> 00:23:16,291
What about my shoulder?

425
00:23:16,375 --> 00:23:17,376
The other side…

426
00:23:18,752 --> 00:23:19,795
What is it?

427
00:23:20,379 --> 00:23:22,923
Uh… You know what? Never mind.

428
00:23:23,007 --> 00:23:26,301
You think helping is crossing a line,
so I'm not going to say anything.

429
00:23:27,678 --> 00:23:30,139
-But that's going to bite, though.
-What?

430
00:23:32,099 --> 00:23:34,393
[exclaiming]

431
00:23:34,977 --> 00:23:37,855
Don't move. It's venomous.

432
00:23:37,938 --> 00:23:41,358
Help me with this. Now!

433
00:23:41,442 --> 00:23:45,612
I want to help, but I have to be careful.

434
00:23:45,696 --> 00:23:46,864
What?

435
00:23:47,448 --> 00:23:49,658
You see,
I learned something thanks to you.

436
00:23:49,742 --> 00:23:52,036
No matter how much someone's struggling,

437
00:23:52,119 --> 00:23:55,289
helping when they don't ask for it
is crossing a line.

438
00:23:55,372 --> 00:23:57,958
It's trying to get in!

439
00:23:58,042 --> 00:23:59,209
Hurry and do something!

440
00:23:59,293 --> 00:24:01,003
What can I do? I can't cross the line.

441
00:24:02,087 --> 00:24:04,131
-[stammers] Cross it.
-What?

442
00:24:04,214 --> 00:24:06,550
Please cross the line!

443
00:24:07,134 --> 00:24:08,719
-Damn it…
-Cross it?

444
00:24:08,802 --> 00:24:11,346
-Cross it. It just crawled inside!
-[exclaims]

445
00:24:11,430 --> 00:24:12,973
-Get it out.
-Just so we're clear,

446
00:24:13,057 --> 00:24:14,349
you said to cross it.

447
00:24:14,433 --> 00:24:17,102
Put your hands inside and take it out.

448
00:24:17,186 --> 00:24:19,146
It's way inside!

449
00:24:19,229 --> 00:24:20,814
-Lower!
-Where? Okay.

450
00:24:20,898 --> 00:24:22,858
-Oh, come on!
-Okay.

451
00:24:22,941 --> 00:24:25,277
-[Jiui exclaims]
-[Hari grunting]

452
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,863
-It's not there. What?
-Uh, Ms. Hari, it went down.

453
00:24:27,946 --> 00:24:28,947
Right now…

454
00:24:29,031 --> 00:24:31,700
-Left waist!
-Darn it!
STYLE
::cue()

455
00:24:31,784 --> 00:24:32,993
-[gasps]
-[Hari] Stand still!

456
00:24:33,077 --> 00:24:34,536
[Jiui] Oh, come on!

457
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:36,663
[exclaims] I think it bit me.

458
00:24:36,747 --> 00:24:37,748
That was my nail.

459
00:24:39,083 --> 00:24:40,876
Stop playing around, seriously!

460
00:24:40,959 --> 00:24:42,127
I'm not.

461
00:24:42,211 --> 00:24:45,214
-[breathing heavily]
-Oh, oh! Here it is. Hold still.

462
00:24:46,256 --> 00:24:48,092
-I caught it.
-You caught it?

463
00:24:49,843 --> 00:24:51,261
[exclaims]

464
00:24:51,345 --> 00:24:53,055
Shouldn't we trap that guy somewhere?

465
00:24:53,138 --> 00:24:55,349
You said it's venomous.
What if it bites someone?

466
00:24:55,432 --> 00:24:56,934
-Why would we do that?
-Damn it.

467
00:24:57,017 --> 00:24:59,436
-They don't bite if you leave them alone.
-[sighs]

468
00:25:01,814 --> 00:25:04,733
Dr. Do, you owe me one now.
Pay me back later.

469
00:25:07,402 --> 00:25:08,695
But…

470
00:25:08,779 --> 00:25:10,364
But that guy's venomous.

471
00:25:12,991 --> 00:25:15,536
Its fangs were terrifying. Did you see?

472
00:25:15,619 --> 00:25:17,704
[thunder rumbling]

473
00:25:20,290 --> 00:25:23,210
[Jiui panting]

474
00:25:23,293 --> 00:25:25,087
This place…

475
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:29,216
[both groan]

476
00:25:29,299 --> 00:25:30,634
[Jiui] This is…

477
00:25:36,473 --> 00:25:39,101
Uh, are you sure this is the place?

478
00:25:39,184 --> 00:25:40,936
It doesn't look like anyone lives here.

479
00:25:41,019 --> 00:25:43,147
This has to be the place.

480
00:25:44,898 --> 00:25:46,608
Just a second.

481
00:25:46,692 --> 00:25:47,776
[Hari grunts]

482
00:25:47,860 --> 00:25:49,987
DO NOT ENTER

483
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:51,738
[door creaks]

484
00:25:51,822 --> 00:25:56,034
Mr. Kim Jeongbae,
we're here from the public health center.

485
00:25:57,369 --> 00:25:59,204
Mr. Kim Jeongbae, are you home?

486
00:26:02,583 --> 00:26:04,668
I'm pretty sure this is the place.

487
00:26:05,919 --> 00:26:07,796
Hold on.

488
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:10,841
[stammers] Are you going in?
That would be a bad idea.

489
00:26:11,425 --> 00:26:14,136
She said it's a patient
who was treated for cancer recently.

490
00:26:15,179 --> 00:26:18,599
If you're going to cross any lines,
you have to make it count.

491
00:26:18,682 --> 00:26:20,267
Especially when saving someone.

492
00:26:22,477 --> 00:26:23,812
[stammers, grunts]

493
00:26:29,568 --> 00:26:31,653
-[thunder rumbling]
-Oh, man…

494
00:26:32,404 --> 00:26:34,281
Hey, Ms. Yuk?

495
00:26:34,364 --> 00:26:36,450
It doesn't look like anyone's here,

496
00:26:36,533 --> 00:26:38,243
so let's come back for them next time.

497
00:26:38,327 --> 00:26:40,287
-Mr. Kim Jeongbae!
-Come on.

498
00:26:40,829 --> 00:26:42,372
Mr. Kim Jeongbae?

499
00:26:45,375 --> 00:26:46,376
Let's go inside.

500
00:26:46,460 --> 00:26:48,295
Wait, Ms. Yuk. Why would you go in there?

501
00:26:48,378 --> 00:26:50,631
How dare you enter my home
without permission?

502
00:26:52,758 --> 00:26:53,926
Who the hell are you?

503
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:56,678
We're from the Public Health Center.

504
00:26:56,762 --> 00:26:59,598
Your daughter said
she couldn't get in touch with you--

505
00:26:59,681 --> 00:27:01,099
Get lost!

506
00:27:01,850 --> 00:27:02,935
Yes, sir.

507
00:27:04,770 --> 00:27:08,273
Now that we know he's fine, let's go.
Hurry up.

508
00:27:08,357 --> 00:27:11,318
Since we're here,
how about a simple checkup? I think that…

509
00:27:11,401 --> 00:27:13,195
What else do we need to check?

510
00:27:13,278 --> 00:27:14,696
…would be a good idea.

511
00:27:17,366 --> 00:27:18,367
But…

512
00:27:18,992 --> 00:27:20,494
he's smoking.

513
00:27:23,497 --> 00:27:25,123
[♪ somber music plays]

514
00:27:25,207 --> 00:27:26,208
Sir.

515
00:27:26,875 --> 00:27:31,463
I heard you recently had surgery,
but you're smoking right now.

516
00:27:31,546 --> 00:27:35,509
That's why your daughter was so worried
and called us.

517
00:27:37,636 --> 00:27:38,637
So what?

518
00:27:39,262 --> 00:27:41,181
Get the hell out before you regret it.

519
00:27:43,350 --> 00:27:45,727
-[lighter clicks]
-We have to go, Ms. Yuk.

520
00:27:45,811 --> 00:27:48,105
-I feel sorry for your daughter.
-Ms. Yuk?

521
00:27:49,147 --> 00:27:52,651
She's been losing sleep over her dad,
who doesn't even care about his own life.

522
00:27:52,734 --> 00:27:54,987
Why get the surgery
if you're going to act like this?

523
00:27:59,449 --> 00:28:02,035
I'm going to contact your daughter.

524
00:28:02,119 --> 00:28:04,371
She needs to know
what kind of state her dad's in.

525
00:28:04,454 --> 00:28:07,833
That way, she'll get to decide
whether to give up on her dad or not.

526
00:28:14,965 --> 00:28:18,135
[♪ tense music plays]

527
00:28:18,218 --> 00:28:20,554
Say one word to my daughter,

528
00:28:20,637 --> 00:28:22,347
-and I'll really kill you.
-Whoa! Sir!

529
00:28:22,431 --> 00:28:24,933
I guess you are ashamed,
seeing as you're angry.

530
00:28:25,017 --> 00:28:27,102
[Jiui] We're sorry. Come with me, Ms. Yuk.

531
00:28:27,185 --> 00:28:28,895
-Sorry, sir.
-I'm not done talking!

532
00:28:28,979 --> 00:28:30,814
-[Jiui] Hurry up!
-[Hari] What are you doing?

533
00:28:30,897 --> 00:28:32,816
What's wrong with you?

534
00:28:33,483 --> 00:28:35,068
-What?
-Come with me.

535
00:28:35,152 --> 00:28:36,945
What on earth are you doing right now?

536
00:28:37,029 --> 00:28:38,030
What?

537
00:28:38,113 --> 00:28:42,242
Don't you know that bringing up smoking
with a cancer patient only riles them up?

538
00:28:42,325 --> 00:28:43,994
I'm just frustrated!

539
00:28:46,329 --> 00:28:47,497
Why would it make you…

540
00:28:48,957 --> 00:28:50,167
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

541
00:28:50,250 --> 00:28:53,420
[owl hooting]

542
00:28:53,503 --> 00:28:55,338
[insects chittering]

543
00:28:59,676 --> 00:29:02,846
Hey, what was that about earlier?

544
00:29:06,183 --> 00:29:08,393
That man still has a chance.

545
00:29:10,437 --> 00:29:15,317
How could someone try so hard
to ruin a second chance at life like that?

546
00:29:16,151 --> 00:29:19,154
Not everyone can get a second chance.

547
00:29:19,946 --> 00:29:23,492
Some people try their hardest to live,
but end up dying anyway.

548
00:29:24,659 --> 00:29:26,536
If I were that man…

549
00:29:28,038 --> 00:29:30,248
I'd try to live seeing only good things,

550
00:29:30,332 --> 00:29:32,542
doing good deeds,
and thinking good thoughts.

551
00:29:34,169 --> 00:29:35,712
So I can live for a long time.

552
00:29:36,922 --> 00:29:39,800
[♪ mournful music plays]

553
00:29:46,723 --> 00:29:48,809
CHAVOXIFEN
CHAVOXIFEN CITRATE

554
00:29:55,232 --> 00:29:57,359
[Jiui stammers] There must be a way.

555
00:29:57,442 --> 00:29:59,027
There's no such thing.

556
00:29:59,861 --> 00:30:01,613
That's not true. It's too soon to--

557
00:30:01,696 --> 00:30:03,782
What can we do now? The sun's gone down.

558
00:30:03,865 --> 00:30:05,992
-[animal howls in distance]
-What?

559
00:30:06,076 --> 00:30:08,578
I think we're lost.

560
00:30:09,621 --> 00:30:11,373
-What?
-[bird squawks]

561
00:30:11,456 --> 00:30:13,208
-Oh, crap! [sighs]
-Right?

562
00:30:15,502 --> 00:30:17,504
[animal howls in distance]

563
00:30:17,587 --> 00:30:18,797
[Jiui] Huh?

564
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,298
What do we do?

565
00:30:20,382 --> 00:30:22,634
Why are you asking me that?

566
00:30:22,717 --> 00:30:25,220
-[♪ mysterious music plays]
-Oh, man…

567
00:30:25,303 --> 00:30:26,805
-[rustling]
-[bird squawks]

568
00:30:26,888 --> 00:30:28,557
[both gasp]

569
00:30:30,016 --> 00:30:31,017
Oh…

570
00:30:33,979 --> 00:30:35,105
-[exclaims]
-[rattling]

571
00:30:35,188 --> 00:30:36,606
-What is that?
-What is it?

572
00:30:36,690 --> 00:30:38,567
Never mind.
I thought it was something else.

573
00:30:38,650 --> 00:30:39,651
Come on!

574
00:30:43,113 --> 00:30:46,032
Aim the flashlight properly!

575
00:30:46,116 --> 00:30:48,076
You should be aiming it properly, okay?

576
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:51,872
Didn't you learn in science class
that you're supposed to raise it high

577
00:30:51,955 --> 00:30:53,915
so that the light spreads more?

578
00:30:53,999 --> 00:30:55,000
Darn it…

579
00:30:55,083 --> 00:30:59,129
How can you talk science when you
can't even see what's under your feet?

580
00:31:00,589 --> 00:31:02,340
Are you sure we're going the right way?

581
00:31:03,008 --> 00:31:04,009
Oh…

582
00:31:04,593 --> 00:31:07,512
I think I saw this tree earlier.

583
00:31:08,930 --> 00:31:11,057
Is this place haunted by ghosts?

584
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:14,436
That's strange.
I thought we were going the right way.

585
00:31:14,519 --> 00:31:16,354
[stammers] Ghosts?

586
00:31:17,522 --> 00:31:18,732
Yes, ghosts.

587
00:31:18,815 --> 00:31:20,609
Oh, come on! You scared me!

588
00:31:21,276 --> 00:31:23,695
Is my face really that scary?

589
00:31:23,778 --> 00:31:25,655
I've seen worse, but I'm bearing with it.

590
00:31:27,866 --> 00:31:31,369
[breathing heavily] I don't think
we'll find our way out at this rate.

591
00:31:31,453 --> 00:31:32,996
Let's split up and look around.

592
00:31:34,289 --> 00:31:35,290
Hey.

593
00:31:35,373 --> 00:31:36,833
[wind howling]

594
00:31:36,917 --> 00:31:38,210
Ms. Yuk!

595
00:31:38,293 --> 00:31:41,546
Uh, split up? I don't want to! [groans]

596
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:45,050
[stammers] I don't want that.
Let's stay together.

597
00:31:45,133 --> 00:31:47,719
We won't find the way like this, so--

598
00:31:47,802 --> 00:31:49,221
Let's just stay together.

599
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:53,558
Is it because you're scared?

600
00:31:56,937 --> 00:31:57,938
[sighs]

601
00:31:58,021 --> 00:32:01,816
Wow, it's one thing
after another with you.

602
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:04,027
-[stammers, grunts]
-[vehicle approaches]

603
00:32:05,070 --> 00:32:06,655
-Oh…
-Huh?

604
00:32:18,250 --> 00:32:21,336
-[Hari gasps] Dr. Chiyeon!
-What are you doing here?

605
00:32:22,212 --> 00:32:23,672
You didn't return, so here I am.

606
00:32:24,381 --> 00:32:27,050
With the sun setting
and the boats no longer running.

607
00:32:27,133 --> 00:32:30,345
-[gasps, chuckles]
-[sighs] Man, I'm so relieved.

608
00:32:31,763 --> 00:32:32,973
[Hari chuckles]

609
00:32:39,479 --> 00:32:40,689
-Hop on.
-Okay.

610
00:32:44,317 --> 00:32:47,445
Oh… How should I get on?

611
00:32:49,447 --> 00:32:50,824
Should I get on down there?

612
00:32:51,449 --> 00:32:52,909
Okay. Sure.

613
00:32:52,993 --> 00:32:54,327
Keep backing up.

614
00:32:54,411 --> 00:32:56,538
Good, just like that.

615
00:32:56,621 --> 00:32:58,581
Yes, just keep backing up.

616
00:33:00,542 --> 00:33:02,085
But are you sure I can get on?
STYLE
::cue()

617
00:33:02,168 --> 00:33:03,837
I don't think I'd fit.

618
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:06,006
Another ride will come.
This is a two-seater.

619
00:33:06,715 --> 00:33:09,384
-Wait a second!
-I'll see you later.

620
00:33:10,010 --> 00:33:11,594
[Jiui] I said wait a second!

621
00:33:11,678 --> 00:33:12,929
Take me with you!

622
00:33:14,180 --> 00:33:15,181
Hey!

623
00:33:16,349 --> 00:33:17,475
I'm scared!

624
00:33:17,559 --> 00:33:18,643
Come on.

625
00:33:25,442 --> 00:33:27,193
Are you sure he'll be okay?

626
00:33:27,277 --> 00:33:28,945
He seems to be a scaredy-cat.

627
00:33:29,029 --> 00:33:30,322
He's a big boy.

628
00:33:31,573 --> 00:33:33,366
-Hold on tight.
-What?

629
00:33:34,367 --> 00:33:35,452
Oh, okay.

630
00:33:39,414 --> 00:33:42,042
-Not there. I meant the handles.
-What?

631
00:33:44,085 --> 00:33:46,463
Oh. Um, uh, right.

632
00:33:48,548 --> 00:33:50,967
You still have a habit
of jumping to conclusions.

633
00:33:52,010 --> 00:33:53,428
Excuse me?

634
00:33:53,511 --> 00:33:55,263
Do you really not remember me?

635
00:33:57,932 --> 00:33:59,017
Wait.

636
00:34:08,318 --> 00:34:09,611
Oh… [chuckles]

637
00:34:10,445 --> 00:34:11,446
I'm sorry.

638
00:34:12,197 --> 00:34:13,615
What?

639
00:34:13,698 --> 00:34:15,075
I have a boyfriend.

640
00:34:16,409 --> 00:34:18,995
-Hey, wait--
-I told you I have a boyfriend.

641
00:34:19,496 --> 00:34:22,832
[♪ comedic music plays]

642
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:30,465
CLIFFSIDE RAW FISH RESTAURANT

643
00:34:33,259 --> 00:34:34,260
[Hyeon sighs]

644
00:34:35,762 --> 00:34:38,014
Just tell me, okay?

645
00:34:40,475 --> 00:34:41,684
If you buy me a meal.

646
00:34:42,310 --> 00:34:43,311
What?

647
00:34:44,562 --> 00:34:48,024
[exclaims] Come on. We've met before?

648
00:34:57,033 --> 00:34:58,451
-Hello.
-[owner] You're here?

649
00:34:58,535 --> 00:34:59,619
-Hey.
-Auntie!

650
00:35:01,079 --> 00:35:02,288
[gasps]

651
00:35:02,372 --> 00:35:03,456
Dr. Do.

652
00:35:06,126 --> 00:35:07,836
How did you get here so fast?

653
00:35:09,170 --> 00:35:10,171
Thanks to you…

654
00:35:10,964 --> 00:35:12,632
I almost ended up dying, okay?

655
00:35:13,466 --> 00:35:14,467
[retches]

656
00:35:16,177 --> 00:35:18,471
[yelps] Ma'am, go slower!

657
00:35:18,555 --> 00:35:20,140
Go slower! [yells]

658
00:35:23,059 --> 00:35:24,227
[screams]

659
00:35:24,310 --> 00:35:26,312
Slower!

660
00:35:27,105 --> 00:35:29,524
[screams]

661
00:35:29,607 --> 00:35:32,944
It was seriously a white-knuckle ride.

662
00:35:33,027 --> 00:35:35,071
Cheer… [grunts] …up!

663
00:35:35,155 --> 00:35:36,239
Here.

664
00:35:37,532 --> 00:35:38,533
You're drinking?

665
00:35:39,242 --> 00:35:41,327
You're meant to drink on days like this.

666
00:35:42,203 --> 00:35:43,580
[owner] You're here?

667
00:35:43,663 --> 00:35:45,081
-[Jangsu] Yes.
-Hey, welcome.

668
00:35:45,749 --> 00:35:46,750
What's this?

669
00:35:47,917 --> 00:35:49,294
Oh, my.

670
00:35:49,377 --> 00:35:52,630
I see Dr. Stickler was here.

671
00:35:52,714 --> 00:35:55,550
The great doctor who won't give
proper prescriptions

672
00:35:55,633 --> 00:35:57,969
because he suspects
his patients of foul play.

673
00:35:58,052 --> 00:35:59,429
That's right.

674
00:36:00,388 --> 00:36:05,560
You see, just like you have your rules,

675
00:36:05,643 --> 00:36:08,229
we have our own rules here in Pyeondongdo.

676
00:36:08,855 --> 00:36:10,482
For every new arrival,

677
00:36:10,565 --> 00:36:14,235
our youth association determines
who's the senior and the junior

678
00:36:14,319 --> 00:36:16,821
by having a drink-off.

679
00:36:17,447 --> 00:36:19,949
Whoever gets wasted first
becomes the junior,

680
00:36:20,033 --> 00:36:22,786
and must obey the senior's every word.

681
00:36:23,369 --> 00:36:24,579
See where this is going?

682
00:36:25,371 --> 00:36:27,916
That's why the owner here
is my big sister now.

683
00:36:27,999 --> 00:36:30,335
-Right.
-Geumja, my sis!

684
00:36:30,418 --> 00:36:31,419
Gosh, that's so gross.

685
00:36:31,503 --> 00:36:34,088
[Jangsu, captain chuckling]

686
00:36:35,173 --> 00:36:38,718
What do you say?
Would you, Dr. Stickler-for-the-Rules,

687
00:36:38,802 --> 00:36:42,597
like to partake in our ritual
so we can establish a proper hierarchy?

688
00:36:45,225 --> 00:36:46,226
Well…

689
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:49,187
I guess he doesn't have
what it takes. [chuckles]

690
00:36:49,270 --> 00:36:51,064
Is it because all he's done is study?

691
00:36:51,147 --> 00:36:53,608
He's a total nerd. [laughs]

692
00:36:56,152 --> 00:36:58,071
-Let's just go.
-Yeah, let's go.

693
00:36:58,655 --> 00:37:01,199
We have to get back quickly--

694
00:37:01,282 --> 00:37:03,326
If those are the rules here,
I'll give it a go.

695
00:37:04,327 --> 00:37:05,912
Dr. Do, no…

696
00:37:06,579 --> 00:37:07,914
You mean it?

697
00:37:08,414 --> 00:37:09,707
Yes.

698
00:37:11,125 --> 00:37:12,126
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

699
00:37:15,380 --> 00:37:18,716
Those guys, they're not human
when it comes to booze, okay?

700
00:37:19,259 --> 00:37:21,469
They're hounds. Boozehounds.

701
00:37:22,595 --> 00:37:24,472
Gosh, I'm so worried.

702
00:37:26,307 --> 00:37:29,602
A man should be able to drink this much.
Don't you think so?

703
00:37:40,738 --> 00:37:41,906
[sighs]

704
00:37:44,617 --> 00:37:46,077
[Jangsu scoffs, pants]

705
00:37:46,744 --> 00:37:48,580
This here's a creamy soju.

706
00:37:59,841 --> 00:38:00,842
[Jiui sighs]

707
00:38:13,438 --> 00:38:14,731
[gags]

708
00:38:14,814 --> 00:38:15,899
[retches]

709
00:38:19,485 --> 00:38:21,321
-[Jiui sighs]
-[grunts]

710
00:38:22,071 --> 00:38:23,197
-[Jiui sighs]
-[grunts]

711
00:38:23,281 --> 00:38:26,868
I'm not like him.

712
00:38:26,951 --> 00:38:27,952
Not bad.

713
00:38:28,453 --> 00:38:30,038
You can actually hold your liquor.

714
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,546
-[sighs, grunts]
-[sighs, grunts]

715
00:38:40,214 --> 00:38:41,966
You haven't forgotten, have you?

716
00:38:42,050 --> 00:38:43,426
The rules in Pyeondongdo.

717
00:38:43,509 --> 00:38:46,220
Whoever loses this
has to become an obedient little bro.

718
00:38:46,304 --> 00:38:49,140
I'm very curious

719
00:38:49,223 --> 00:38:53,686
how much of an obedient little bro
Dr. Stickler over here will be

720
00:38:53,770 --> 00:38:55,396
once I beat him.

721
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:57,607
[chortles]

722
00:39:07,075 --> 00:39:08,076
[gags]

723
00:39:09,535 --> 00:39:10,536
[glass thuds]

724
00:39:11,329 --> 00:39:15,625
[Jangsu groans, retches]

725
00:39:15,708 --> 00:39:17,126
[Jiui] I'm also curious…

726
00:39:17,752 --> 00:39:19,545
[clamoring]

727
00:39:19,629 --> 00:39:21,297
[spectator] Wow, look at him go!

728
00:39:21,381 --> 00:39:22,924
…what I'm like when I'm drunk.

729
00:39:23,007 --> 00:39:29,305
2013 HANGUK UNIVERSITY
PRE-MED SEMESTER KICK-OFF PARTY

730
00:39:30,139 --> 00:39:33,142
[♪ triumphant music plays]

731
00:39:38,815 --> 00:39:39,899
[Geumja] He won.

732
00:39:40,441 --> 00:39:41,776
He actually won.

733
00:39:43,236 --> 00:39:44,946
-[gasps]
-[Hari] Mm-hmm.

734
00:39:47,573 --> 00:39:48,574
Another?

735
00:39:49,367 --> 00:39:51,369
[panting]

736
00:39:53,705 --> 00:39:56,457
[exclaims, slurring] What the…

737
00:39:57,166 --> 00:39:58,626
Do you know who I am?

738
00:39:59,627 --> 00:40:02,213
I'm the Bloodstained Fist
of Pyeondongdo, you prick!

739
00:40:06,592 --> 00:40:07,802
Huh?

740
00:40:07,885 --> 00:40:09,762
[whimpers] Blood…

741
00:40:13,891 --> 00:40:14,976
[whimpers]

742
00:40:16,227 --> 00:40:17,270
[groans]

743
00:40:28,906 --> 00:40:31,868
[groans, slurring] What's this?

744
00:40:31,951 --> 00:40:34,162
What happened to my hand?

745
00:40:41,127 --> 00:40:42,587
Forceps, please. [sighs]

746
00:40:46,549 --> 00:40:47,550
[Jangsu groans]

747
00:40:49,343 --> 00:40:51,679
[groaning]

748
00:40:51,763 --> 00:40:53,723
Looks like you can feel your hand.

749
00:40:53,806 --> 00:40:55,058
[Hari] What should we do?

750
00:40:55,725 --> 00:40:59,145
I think we can stitch him up.
There doesn't seem to be any nerve damage.

751
00:40:59,812 --> 00:41:01,397
You're going to stitch him up?

752
00:41:02,190 --> 00:41:05,318
Out of the question. We had alcohol.

753
00:41:05,401 --> 00:41:07,695
This could cause huge problems
down the line,
STYLE
::cue()

754
00:41:07,779 --> 00:41:09,614
and it has happened before.

755
00:41:13,034 --> 00:41:16,579
Article 7 of the code of medical ethics.
A physician shall not practice medicine

756
00:41:16,662 --> 00:41:19,665
while under the influence
of alcohol, narcotics, or drugs,

757
00:41:19,749 --> 00:41:23,127
or in a physical or mental state
that may cause harm to the patient's life

758
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:25,046
or physical well-being.

759
00:41:25,129 --> 00:41:27,632
If they complain later
that a drunk doctor operated on him,

760
00:41:27,715 --> 00:41:29,383
you'll both be in big trouble.

761
00:41:31,094 --> 00:41:33,304
Let's have him go
to the hospital early tomorrow.

762
00:41:33,387 --> 00:41:35,515
[snoring]

763
00:41:36,516 --> 00:41:38,392
He definitely won't go.

764
00:41:39,268 --> 00:41:41,020
The boats head out tomorrow,

765
00:41:41,646 --> 00:41:44,816
and missing just a single day
is a huge loss in anchovy fishing.

766
00:41:45,942 --> 00:41:47,193
But he still needs… [sighs]

767
00:41:47,276 --> 00:41:50,696
[snoring continues]

768
00:41:51,489 --> 00:41:53,616
[inhales sharply]
Let's do it tomorrow morning.

769
00:41:53,699 --> 00:41:55,576
It just needs to be done within 24 hours.

770
00:41:55,660 --> 00:41:58,996
For the record, I clearly warned you
that this may cause problems later.

771
00:41:59,080 --> 00:42:01,666
Don't worry. I'll take responsibility.

772
00:42:06,546 --> 00:42:07,672
You should go home too.

773
00:42:11,884 --> 00:42:14,887
[♪ contemplative music plays]

774
00:42:46,419 --> 00:42:47,420
[Hari] Dr. Do.

775
00:42:51,090 --> 00:42:52,091
Dr. Do.

776
00:42:53,092 --> 00:42:54,093
Yes…

777
00:42:54,802 --> 00:42:55,803
Yes?

778
00:42:55,887 --> 00:42:58,472
Um, it's been eight hours.

779
00:42:58,556 --> 00:43:00,933
Don't you think we're good to start now?

780
00:43:01,017 --> 00:43:03,352
Let's treat him quickly
so you can get some rest too.

781
00:43:04,812 --> 00:43:07,398
You're still here? Why?

782
00:43:08,441 --> 00:43:10,276
Because we still have a patient.

783
00:44:04,205 --> 00:44:06,082
Doesn't he get on your nerves?

784
00:44:08,292 --> 00:44:09,627
He filed a complaint,

785
00:44:09,710 --> 00:44:13,005
forced you to drink alcohol,
and picked on you.

786
00:44:13,089 --> 00:44:15,549
Um… [sighs]

787
00:44:15,633 --> 00:44:17,051
You're right. I don't like him.

788
00:44:17,134 --> 00:44:19,053
[inhales sharply] But…

789
00:44:20,471 --> 00:44:21,973
like him or not,

790
00:44:23,099 --> 00:44:24,767
lacerations are lacerations.

791
00:44:26,602 --> 00:44:27,812
Oh…

792
00:44:33,401 --> 00:44:35,027
[exclaims]

793
00:44:35,111 --> 00:44:36,529
What now?

794
00:44:37,405 --> 00:44:38,406
[Hari chuckles]

795
00:44:40,116 --> 00:44:42,285
-[exclaims]
-[chuckles]

796
00:44:42,368 --> 00:44:44,954
[both laugh]

797
00:44:46,163 --> 00:44:47,164
[sniffles]
STYLE
::cue()

798
00:45:03,347 --> 00:45:05,433
[Jangsu] What the heck is this?

799
00:45:05,516 --> 00:45:08,644
What on earth happened to my hand?

800
00:45:10,313 --> 00:45:12,606
You were drunk yesterday
and broke a mirror,

801
00:45:12,690 --> 00:45:14,317
so I stitched up the wounds.

802
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:17,111
Me? Drunk?

803
00:45:18,571 --> 00:45:21,657
Get a load of this hotshot from Seoul,

804
00:45:21,741 --> 00:45:23,534
blaming me for something I didn't do!

805
00:45:23,617 --> 00:45:25,828
My boat's heading out today!

806
00:45:25,911 --> 00:45:28,789
How am I supposed to
pull the nets with my hand like this?

807
00:45:29,665 --> 00:45:31,959
I won't let this slide, okay?

808
00:45:32,043 --> 00:45:36,172
I'm going to sue you
for also causing me emotional--

809
00:45:36,255 --> 00:45:38,632
What are you going to do
if you don't let it slide?

810
00:45:38,716 --> 00:45:39,717
[Ms. Hwang] Mr. Park!

811
00:45:40,885 --> 00:45:43,262
Everyone knows
you become an animal when you drink.

812
00:45:43,346 --> 00:45:44,805
I'm so sick of this.

813
00:45:44,889 --> 00:45:47,016
Why come all this way
to bitch at the doctors

814
00:45:47,099 --> 00:45:49,060
who are performing their sacred duties?

815
00:45:49,143 --> 00:45:51,562
-No, that's not--
-Don't talk back to your chief.

816
00:45:53,105 --> 00:45:55,566
Pulling the chief card on me.

817
00:45:55,649 --> 00:45:56,817
Like you always do.

818
00:45:56,901 --> 00:45:58,235
[Mr. Park sighs]

819
00:45:58,819 --> 00:46:00,821
-Dr. Do Jiui, come over here.
-Oh.

820
00:46:01,447 --> 00:46:02,448
What's this?

821
00:46:02,531 --> 00:46:05,368
[Mr. Park] This right here is maeuntang.

822
00:46:05,451 --> 00:46:07,286
-[Ms. Hwang] Oh, goodness.
-[Mr. Park chuckles]

823
00:46:07,370 --> 00:46:09,997
It's made with all-natural ingredients,
so it'll be delicious.

824
00:46:10,081 --> 00:46:11,415
You should have it for lunch.

825
00:46:11,499 --> 00:46:12,708
Thank you, sir.

826
00:46:12,792 --> 00:46:13,793
[Mr. Park] All right, then.

827
00:46:13,876 --> 00:46:15,628
-Good luck today.
-Thank you.

828
00:46:16,629 --> 00:46:18,130
Stop interfering and come with me.

829
00:46:18,756 --> 00:46:20,925
Chop-chop! Leave.

830
00:46:21,008 --> 00:46:22,009
Come on.

831
00:46:23,427 --> 00:46:24,553
[chuckles]

832
00:46:24,637 --> 00:46:25,638
-Let's go.
-Hey!

833
00:46:25,721 --> 00:46:27,598
-[Ms. Hwang chuckles]
-Thank you, sir!

834
00:46:27,681 --> 00:46:29,725
-[Mr. Park] Bye!
-[Ms. Hwang] Take care!

835
00:46:31,102 --> 00:46:32,103
[Mr. Park] Okay!

836
00:46:33,020 --> 00:46:36,857
[Hari] I think Mr. Lee Jangsu acted out
like that because he was embarrassed.

837
00:46:41,737 --> 00:46:42,905
[Jiui sighs]

838
00:46:44,365 --> 00:46:48,536
He was defeated
in the chief elections for years,

839
00:46:48,619 --> 00:46:52,415
and now he's even lost his title
as the heaviest drinker to you.

840
00:46:53,791 --> 00:46:55,626
But still, taking it out on me…

841
00:46:56,919 --> 00:46:58,462
It's not like it'll solve anything.

842
00:47:00,589 --> 00:47:04,427
It may not solve anything,
but it can mask your embarrassment.

843
00:47:05,886 --> 00:47:09,056
Isn't that the easiest way out
when you want to hide something?

844
00:47:09,140 --> 00:47:10,558
Getting angry.

845
00:47:10,641 --> 00:47:12,643
[♪ contemplative music plays]

846
00:47:13,978 --> 00:47:15,271
[inhales sharply]

847
00:47:15,354 --> 00:47:16,355
In that case…

848
00:47:32,121 --> 00:47:33,873
What do you think Mr. Kim Jeongbae…

849
00:47:36,041 --> 00:47:37,585
wanted to hide?

850
00:47:38,794 --> 00:47:39,795
What?

851
00:47:44,550 --> 00:47:47,178
-I'm going to go see Mr. Kim Jeongbae.
-Me too!

852
00:47:47,261 --> 00:47:48,637
Dr. Do!

853
00:47:48,721 --> 00:47:50,764
What the heck? Are they BFFs already?

854
00:47:53,058 --> 00:47:55,144
[panting]

855
00:47:55,227 --> 00:47:57,271
[thunderclap]

856
00:48:00,065 --> 00:48:01,650
Mr. Kim Jeongbae!

857
00:48:02,985 --> 00:48:04,195
Mr. Kim Jeongbae!

858
00:48:05,821 --> 00:48:06,864
Damn it.

859
00:48:07,865 --> 00:48:10,701
[thunder rumbling]

860
00:48:10,784 --> 00:48:12,244
What the hell is it this time?

861
00:48:12,328 --> 00:48:14,580
Sir, may I take a look at your foot?

862
00:48:14,663 --> 00:48:17,875
-Why would you look at my foot?
-We just need to check really quickly.

863
00:48:17,958 --> 00:48:20,294
Come over here if you've got a death wish.

864
00:48:20,377 --> 00:48:22,129
-[Hari gasps]
-[thunderclap]

865
00:48:22,213 --> 00:48:23,339
Ms. Yuk.

866
00:48:23,422 --> 00:48:25,382
I'm okay. Hurry and take a look at him.

867
00:48:27,301 --> 00:48:29,762
-Let me see your foot.
-What do you think you're doing?

868
00:48:29,845 --> 00:48:31,597
Let go. I said let go of me!

869
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:32,723
I'm sorry. One second!

870
00:48:38,229 --> 00:48:40,064
[exhales sharply]

871
00:48:40,147 --> 00:48:42,775
-You knew you were diabetic, didn't you?
-Diabetic, my ass!

872
00:48:42,858 --> 00:48:44,276
It's just a little bruise!

873
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:45,444
Bruise?

874
00:48:46,195 --> 00:48:47,988
I'm a plastic surgeon,

875
00:48:48,072 --> 00:48:50,533
and I've amputated dozens of toes
during my residency.

876
00:48:50,616 --> 00:48:52,952
You think I can't tell a bruised foot
from a diabetic one?

877
00:48:53,035 --> 00:48:54,578
So what? What do you want me to do?

878
00:48:54,662 --> 00:48:57,039
You have to go to a hospital right now!

879
00:48:59,333 --> 00:49:01,544
If you don't treat this,
you could lose your leg,

880
00:49:01,627 --> 00:49:03,712
and worst case, you could die of sepsis!

881
00:49:04,547 --> 00:49:06,131
-I don't care.
-Sir!

882
00:49:06,215 --> 00:49:08,592
This is my problem,
and I'll handle it myself!

883
00:49:09,510 --> 00:49:10,594
So please,

884
00:49:10,678 --> 00:49:12,846
don't tell my daughter about this,

885
00:49:13,722 --> 00:49:15,558
and pretend you didn't see anything.
STYLE
::cue()

886
00:49:16,267 --> 00:49:17,851
I'm begging you!

887
00:49:21,647 --> 00:49:22,731
No.

888
00:49:26,860 --> 00:49:28,529
I don't think I can do that.

889
00:49:54,305 --> 00:49:57,474
Looks like we'll have to
tell his daughter, right?

890
00:50:02,605 --> 00:50:03,606
Ms. Yuk?

891
00:50:06,108 --> 00:50:07,568
Dr. Do, just a moment.

892
00:50:09,153 --> 00:50:10,237
Please wait here.

893
00:50:10,904 --> 00:50:11,905
What?

894
00:50:13,198 --> 00:50:14,450
Ms. Yuk!

895
00:50:15,909 --> 00:50:17,036
Oh…

896
00:51:08,796 --> 00:51:12,257
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

897
00:51:27,523 --> 00:51:28,857
Dr. Do.

898
00:51:28,941 --> 00:51:29,942
Yes?

899
00:51:33,028 --> 00:51:35,823
Aren't you hungry?
Do you want to have some ramyeon?

900
00:51:35,906 --> 00:51:37,908
[♪ upbeat pop song plays]

901
00:51:40,452 --> 00:51:41,870
-Ramyeon?
-Yeah.

902
00:51:42,913 --> 00:51:43,914
[sniffles]

903
00:51:48,043 --> 00:51:49,044
-Well…
-[sniffles]

904
00:52:06,395 --> 00:52:08,397
[song continues]

905
00:52:17,906 --> 00:52:20,659
Why'd you make it
when I'm the one who suggested it?

906
00:52:22,327 --> 00:52:23,996
This was me repaying my debt.

907
00:52:24,079 --> 00:52:25,080
-Your debt?
-Yeah.

908
00:52:26,749 --> 00:52:27,750
You mean the spider?

909
00:52:29,334 --> 00:52:30,627
Oh, come on.

910
00:52:30,711 --> 00:52:35,132
I saved your life from a venomous spider,
and you want to call it even with this?

911
00:52:35,215 --> 00:52:37,259
No way. I'll get something bigger later.

912
00:52:37,342 --> 00:52:39,261
I already made it for you, okay?

913
00:52:39,344 --> 00:52:40,345
[chuckles]

914
00:52:44,266 --> 00:52:46,310
[knocks on door]

915
00:52:47,978 --> 00:52:49,229
Are we expecting someone?

916
00:52:50,397 --> 00:52:51,398
[Hari gasps]

917
00:52:52,441 --> 00:52:54,234
BREAK ROOM

918
00:53:06,121 --> 00:53:08,832
[thunderclap]

919
00:53:13,587 --> 00:53:14,630
Help me.

920
00:53:16,298 --> 00:53:17,341
Please…

921
00:53:18,217 --> 00:53:19,676
Help me live.

922
00:53:22,221 --> 00:53:24,515
[thunderclap]
STYLE
::cue()

923
00:53:32,731 --> 00:53:34,149
-[Jiui grunts]
-[Hari gasps]

924
00:53:36,527 --> 00:53:37,528
[groans]

925
00:53:41,156 --> 00:53:42,491
How does it look?

926
00:53:44,952 --> 00:53:47,496
The redness is widespread,
and judging by the fluctuance,

927
00:53:47,579 --> 00:53:49,748
it looks like a late-stage abscess.

928
00:53:53,001 --> 00:53:54,002
Let's perform an I&amp;D.

929
00:53:54,086 --> 00:53:55,712
Right. I'll make the preparations.

930
00:54:00,425 --> 00:54:01,552
[sighs]

931
00:54:16,817 --> 00:54:17,860
[Jeongbae] Doctor…

932
00:54:20,279 --> 00:54:22,364
Will I really make it out of this alive?

933
00:54:24,408 --> 00:54:25,576
Of course, sir.

934
00:54:26,869 --> 00:54:27,870
[sighs]

935
00:54:30,289 --> 00:54:31,290
[sighs]

936
00:55:22,299 --> 00:55:24,384
-I'll bring the antibiotics.
-[Jiui] Okay.

937
00:55:39,358 --> 00:55:41,193
Why did you change your mind?

938
00:55:47,574 --> 00:55:50,911
She told me not to feel guilty
for being alive.

939
00:55:54,122 --> 00:55:57,125
She said that would cause
too much pain to those left behind.

940
00:55:58,669 --> 00:56:00,295
That's what that nurse said.

941
00:56:03,006 --> 00:56:05,717
I'm just going to
keep living like this until I die,

942
00:56:05,801 --> 00:56:08,345
so stop harassing me and get lost!

943
00:56:13,183 --> 00:56:16,269
What about the family you leave behind
if you die like this?

944
00:56:17,771 --> 00:56:20,691
Do you think your family
will be able to just go on living?

945
00:56:22,067 --> 00:56:24,486
How do you expect your family
to go on living

946
00:56:25,696 --> 00:56:28,865
if you leave them no chance
to do anything about it?

947
00:56:33,578 --> 00:56:34,871
So, please…

948
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:41,294
Please do it for your daughter, sir.

949
00:56:43,922 --> 00:56:44,923
Okay?

950
00:56:49,678 --> 00:56:53,598
[Jeongbae] What she said
brought me to my senses.

951
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:57,477
When my wife was sick,

952
00:56:58,478 --> 00:57:03,608
that was the one thing
I struggled with the most.

953
00:57:05,986 --> 00:57:09,865
Seeing my wife
consumed by guilt for being alive.

954
00:57:12,242 --> 00:57:13,660
But I…

955
00:57:16,413 --> 00:57:22,461
[sobbing] …have been doing the same thing
to my daughter.

956
00:57:27,966 --> 00:57:30,635
[Jeongbae sobbing, sniffles]
STYLE
::cue()

957
00:57:42,230 --> 00:57:43,356
[sighs]

958
00:57:54,951 --> 00:57:57,120
He seems to have fallen asleep.
What do we do now?

959
00:57:58,789 --> 00:58:00,707
[Jiui] He had a lot of pus in him,

960
00:58:01,416 --> 00:58:04,085
so I think we should
monitor him here a little longer.

961
00:58:05,086 --> 00:58:06,838
Shall we let him sleep for a while?

962
00:58:08,006 --> 00:58:09,007
Yes.

963
00:58:14,805 --> 00:58:15,972
[Hari sighs]

964
00:58:23,146 --> 00:58:24,356
[Hari sighs]

965
00:58:25,065 --> 00:58:27,984
I thought things would be easier
at a public health center,

966
00:58:29,402 --> 00:58:31,947
but I had it better at an ER. [chuckles]

967
00:58:33,532 --> 00:58:34,783
[inhales sharply]

968
00:58:35,617 --> 00:58:36,660
Mmm…

969
00:58:38,453 --> 00:58:42,415
By the way, how did you know
that Mr. Kim Jeongbae was a diabetic?

970
00:58:44,334 --> 00:58:45,335
[inhales sharply]

971
00:58:45,418 --> 00:58:46,419
You said it yourself.

972
00:58:47,963 --> 00:58:52,300
That the easiest way
to hide a secret is to lash out.

973
00:58:54,219 --> 00:58:57,180
[inhales sharply]
For suffering patients with secrets,

974
00:58:57,264 --> 00:58:59,015
the answer is always treatment.

975
00:59:01,059 --> 00:59:02,060
Oh…

976
00:59:07,357 --> 00:59:10,193
-By the way, are you okay?
-Hmm?

977
00:59:11,278 --> 00:59:14,030
Ah… It's fine.
I'm sure it'll heal in no time.

978
00:59:14,114 --> 00:59:15,156
Stay right here.

979
00:59:16,408 --> 00:59:18,201
It's fine. I'm okay.

980
00:59:18,285 --> 00:59:19,619
Just sit back down.

981
00:59:19,703 --> 00:59:23,081
Why leave it like that?
We have medicine and a doctor to help you.

982
00:59:23,164 --> 00:59:24,416
Wait here.

983
00:59:24,499 --> 00:59:25,876
[stammers]

984
00:59:25,959 --> 00:59:27,794
I'm really fine, though…

985
00:59:34,759 --> 00:59:35,760
[softly] Let's see.

986
00:59:39,180 --> 00:59:40,348
Man, that must have stung.

987
00:59:47,188 --> 00:59:49,566
[♪ romantic ballad playing]

988
00:59:56,990 --> 00:59:57,991
Dr. Do.

989
01:00:03,079 --> 01:00:07,834
You said treatment was the answer
to a suffering patient's secrets, right?

990
01:00:08,710 --> 01:00:09,711
I did.

991
01:00:15,717 --> 01:00:17,344
Then what's your secret?

992
01:00:21,014 --> 01:00:22,057
What?

993
01:00:22,891 --> 01:00:24,392
You're also hurting.

994
01:00:25,518 --> 01:00:28,855
Every time you have to get on a boat,
you get so anxious you need medication.

995
01:00:28,939 --> 01:00:31,107
And you get mad
when people try to help you.

996
01:00:33,485 --> 01:00:35,570
Like someone who wants to hide something.

997
01:00:49,292 --> 01:00:50,961
I'm not crossing a line here.

998
01:00:52,796 --> 01:00:54,756
I'm asking as a nurse.

999
01:00:58,009 --> 01:01:00,762
Just like you want to treat me
because you're a doctor…

1000
01:01:03,014 --> 01:01:04,474
I'm a nurse…

1001
01:01:06,810 --> 01:01:09,145
so I want to help you,
since you're suffering.

1002
01:01:10,230 --> 01:01:11,231
Okay?

1003
01:01:16,027 --> 01:01:17,028
[sighs]

1004
01:01:22,617 --> 01:01:24,160
Don't tell me if you don't want to.

1005
01:01:24,244 --> 01:01:26,371
I can just find out myself. [chuckles]

1006
01:01:28,498 --> 01:01:30,375
[song continues]
STYLE
::cue()

1007
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:48,184
[breathes shakily]

1008
01:01:51,438 --> 01:01:52,439
[sighs]

1009
01:01:53,231 --> 01:01:57,068
[ship horn blows]

1010
01:01:58,737 --> 01:02:02,240
When you arrive on the mainland,
your daughter will be waiting for you.

1011
01:02:03,658 --> 01:02:05,702
-I'm sorry about everything.
-[Hari chuckles]

1012
01:02:05,785 --> 01:02:07,287
Don't worry about it. [chuckles]

1013
01:02:07,370 --> 01:02:08,872
Good luck with your treatment.

1014
01:02:08,955 --> 01:02:10,206
We'll be waiting for you.

1015
01:02:18,173 --> 01:02:19,299
Thank you.

1016
01:02:20,425 --> 01:02:23,428
[♪ heartfelt music plays]

1017
01:02:26,514 --> 01:02:28,600
Thanks for giving me the courage.

1018
01:02:37,734 --> 01:02:38,818
[sighs]

1019
01:02:46,409 --> 01:02:47,494
Shall we go?

1020
01:02:49,329 --> 01:02:50,330
Yes.

1021
01:02:59,464 --> 01:03:03,051
[ship horn blows]

1022
01:03:03,635 --> 01:03:06,096
-About Mr. Kim Jeongbae…
-Oh?

1023
01:03:07,013 --> 01:03:09,891
Maybe we should have given him
some meds for seasickness.

1024
01:03:10,433 --> 01:03:11,434
Huh?

1025
01:03:12,936 --> 01:03:14,896
Well, getting seasick wouldn't be good.

1026
01:03:16,064 --> 01:03:18,191
He works on a boat for a living, remember?

1027
01:03:20,110 --> 01:03:21,861
-Oh…
-[chuckles]

1028
01:03:21,945 --> 01:03:23,363
-Yes.
-You're right.

1029
01:03:23,446 --> 01:03:27,117
PYEONDONGDO FISHING

1030
01:03:36,501 --> 01:03:38,545
Hello, Mr. Park!

1031
01:03:38,628 --> 01:03:40,088
-[Jiui] Mr. Park.
-Have you been somewhere?

1032
01:03:40,171 --> 01:03:41,714
[Jiui] Are you feeling better?

1033
01:03:46,719 --> 01:03:49,722
[♪ upbeat music plays]

1034
01:03:54,686 --> 01:03:56,229
You lying bastard!

1035
01:03:56,312 --> 01:03:57,522
[gasps]

1036
01:04:21,546 --> 01:04:24,299
FOR SUFFERING PATIENTS
WITH SECRETS,

1037
01:04:24,382 --> 01:04:29,387
THE ANSWER IS ALWAYS TREATMENT

1038
01:04:48,990 --> 01:04:52,410
A LITTLE JOKING AROUND ON SET
REALLY BRINGS THE PLACE TO LIFE

1039
01:05:00,501 --> 01:05:03,421
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

1040
01:05:03,504 --> 01:05:05,715
[stammers] Mr. Park, what brings you here?

1041
01:05:05,798 --> 01:05:08,176
-[shouts]
-[Mr. Park] You lying quack!

1042
01:05:08,259 --> 01:05:10,511
Is he seriously trying to ruin my life?

1043
01:05:11,304 --> 01:05:12,722
-[exclaims]
-[Jiui] Hey, Lee Jangsu!

1044
01:05:13,473 --> 01:05:15,183
What did I do wrong just now?

1045
01:05:15,266 --> 01:05:16,434
[screams]

1046
01:05:16,517 --> 01:05:17,560
[Hari] Were you waiting for me?

1047
01:05:17,644 --> 01:05:20,146
We have plenty of time to spare.
Would you like a drink?

1048
01:05:20,230 --> 01:05:22,023
Was that so hard?

1049
01:05:22,106 --> 01:05:25,026
[Jucheon] It's like something out of
a late '80s movie.

1050
01:05:25,109 --> 01:05:27,320
[Hari] Doctor, come with me.

1051
01:05:27,403 --> 01:05:29,822
[Hyeon] Are we really going to sleep
in the same room?

1052
01:05:29,906 --> 01:05:31,115
[Hari] Do you regret it?

1053
01:05:32,951 --> 01:05:34,953
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park

